# Global preferences for Claude Code (confepo)
#
# This is a TEMPLATE. To apply these instructions to EVERY project, activate it:
#     cp ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md.example ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md
# (kept opt-in on purpose — a global CLAUDE.md affects all your repos.)

## Working style
- Be concise. Lead with the answer; expand only as far as the question needs.
- When you have enough to act, act — don't narrate options you won't take.
- Before destructive or outward-facing actions (rm, force-push, deploy, sending
  data to a service), confirm unless clearly authorized.

## This machine
- Ubuntu + i3 (X11) + fish. Default editor: nano. Dotfiles managed by confepo
  (GNU Stow; `confepo update` / `confepo uninstall`).
- Prefer the modern CLI tools that are installed: `eza`, `bat`, `rg`, `fd`, `fzf`,
  `zoxide`, `delta`, `btop`, `duf`.

## Shell scripts
- bash with `set -euo pipefail`; quote expansions; make scripts idempotent and
  shellcheck-clean. Never let an optional step abort a critical one.
- Map package names per package manager; detect tools with `command -v`.

## Delegation
- For non-trivial reviews use the `code-reviewer` agent; for shell work the
  `shell-hardener` agent; commit messages via the `commit` skill.
